"L E S S O N Saxon Math Course 3 Relative Sizes of Sides and Angles of a Triangle Power Up Building Power facts Power Up W mental math a. Algebra: Solve: 2k + 2 = 170 b. Estimation: 205 × 390 c. Fractional Parts: 5 11 of 77 d. Percent: 25% less than $120 is the same as what percent of $120? e. Rate: $100 per week is about how many dollars per year? f. Geometry: The Pythagorean Theorem applies to all A acute triangles. B right triangles. C obtuse triangles. g. Measurement: How long would 10 bolts be? INCH     h. Calculation: 81 ÷ 3, ÷ 3, ÷ 3, ÷ 3, ÷ 3 problem solvings The number 1 can be written as the difference of two prime numbers (3 – 2). The numbers 2 and 3 can also be written as the difference of two prime numbers (5 – 3 and 5 – 2, respectively). If possible, write each of the numbers 4, 5, 6, and 7 as the differences of two prime numbers. New Concept Increasing Knowledge Refer to △ABC below. Listed in order of size, the angles of △ABC are ∠A, then ∠B, and ∠C. Listed in order of length, the sides of △ABC are side BC, side CA, and side AB. M! "" # ! M"" M# ""# #! !"" Notice that the side opposite the smallest angle is the shortest side (side BC and ∠A). Likewise, the side opposite the longest angle is the longest side (side AB and ∠C)."
"The order of lengths of sides of a triangle when written from shortest to longest corresponds to the order of the sides’ opposite angles when written from smallest to largest. Example 1 List the sides of this triangle in order from shortest to longest. Solution The sum of the interior angles of a triangle is 180º, so m∠P = 60º. Thus, the angles in order from smallest to largest are ∠ R, ∠ P, and ∠ Q. The lengths of the sides opposite these angles follow the same order. The side opposite ∠R is side PQ, which is the shortest side. We list the three sides in order of length. side PQ (or QP), side QR (or RQ), side RP (or PR) Example 2 The lengths of sides of  ABC are given. List the angles in order of size from smallest to largest. Solution The shortest side is opposite the smallest angle. Since side AB is the shortest side, the smallest angle is ∠ C . We list the angles in order from smallest to largest. C,  A , B Example 3 If we know the length of side AC, how could we find the length of side WY? Find WY if AC = 6 cm. # ! "" Ɓ Ɓ ␀CM Ɓ Ɓ ␀CM Ɓ Ɓ "" ! #   "
"Saxon Math Course 3 Solution The sum of the angle measures of a triangle is 180º, so we know that m∠A = 55º and m∠X = 40º. We see that the three angles of △ WXY are congruent to the corresponding angles of △ ABC. Therefore, the two triangles are similar and their lengths of sides are proportional. Thinking Skill Explain How do we determine the scale factor for example 3? The scale factor from the larger triangle to the smaller triangle is 6 8 (or 3 4 ). If we know AC, we can find WY by multiplying AC by the scale factor or by solving a proportion. We show both methods for finding WY when AC is 6 cm. Multiplying by Scale Factor : Solve Proportion: WY = scale factor × AC 6  6 x  3 4  6 8x = 36 = 4.5 cm x = 4.5 cm Practice Set For a and b refer to figure ABCD. a. Find the measure of ∠ CBD, ∠ DBA, and ∠ DAB. b. Arrange these segments in order from shortest to longest. AB, AD, BD, BC, DC, c. Classify Which angle in △ WXY is the smallest angle? d. Analyze Refer to the triangles in example 3. Find WY if AC is 6.4 cm. Written Practice Strengthening Concepts 1. (48) Connie was confused and filled forty-four percent of the flower pots with flour. If she did not fill 28 of the pots, how many pots were there in all? 2. (3, 4) The local art museum purchased one of Connie’s flour-filled pots for $700. It is a hit, so Connie makes $5 per autograph. If she signs 40 autographs, how much money does she make in all? * 3. (89) Samantha had 21 nickels and dimes. They totaled $1.60. Two equations that show this information are shown below. u + d = 21 5u + 10d = 160 e Use this information to help you find and check the numbers of nickels and dimes Samantha has. ␀M ␀M ␀M # ! $ "" Ɓ Ɓ"
