"Saxon Math Course 3 New Concept Increasing Knowledge A complex fraction is a fraction containing one or more fractions in the numerator or denominator. Each of the following is a complex fraction: It is customary to express the numerator and denominator of a fraction with integers when possible. We will describe two methods for simplifying a complex fraction. One method is to use the identity property of multiplication (multiply the numerator and denominator of the fraction by a common denominator). Example 1 Simplify: Solution Thinking Skill Analyze What is the result of multiplying the numerator and denominator by the common denominator? The complex fraction is composed of the fractions 1 5 and 2 3 which have a common denominator of 15. We multiply the complex fraction by 15 15. We perform the multiplication in the numerator and the multiplication in the denominator separately. 515   Notice that we multiplied the complex fraction by a fraction equivalent to 1, so the resulting fraction is equal to the original complex fraction. An alternative method for simplifying some complex fractions is to treat the complex fraction as a fraction division problem. We can express the division problem with a division sign instead of a fraction bar. dividend divisor 5  2 We simplify the division using the method described in Lesson 22. 5  2 3  1 5  3 2  3 Example 2 Simplify: 2  1 3  1 Solution We cannot cancel because the fractions in the numerator and denominator are added, not multiplied. First we simplify the numerator and denominator by adding the fractions."
"2  1 3  1  Now we can express the complex fraction as a division of fractions. 6  7 6  12 7  10 We could have used the method of multiplying by the common denominator (12) even before adding. 12  (1 2  1 3) (1 3  1 4) Multiplied by 12 22  41211 32  31211 Distributive property 6  4 4  3 Simplified Simplified Example 3 Change 284 7% to a fraction and simplify. Solution A percent is a fraction that has a denominator of 100. Thus 284 7% is Next, we write both the numerator and denominator as fractions. Now we multiply the complex fraction by 7 7. 17(200 71 ) 7(100 1 )  200 700  2 Practice Set Simplify. a. b. 30 c. 2  1 2  1 Change each percent to a fraction and simplify: d. 142 7% e. 81 3% f. 41 6%"
